			<br>Once a century, whoever wins the competition between the living and the dead gets the right to open the door to a world where any wish can be granted.
			<br>All the events of the first book of the cycle - "The Game at Twilight" - take place under the cover of darkness.
			<br>And the reader begins to plunge into this dark atmosphere just by looking at the cover, beautifully drawn by Olga Zakis.
